            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.carbonbrief.org/in-depth-qa-the-ipccs-sixth-assessment-on-how-to-tackle-climate-change",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " on the key findings of the report. Some takeaways that stuck out:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Carbon emissions have continued to increase over the past decade, but increased more slowly than in the preceding decade.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
            "value": 1,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "If countries follow their existing climate pledges, the world is still on track to overshoot the Paris Agreement goal limiting warming to 1.5 degrees Celsius (2.7 degrees Fahrenheit) by the end of the decade.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
            "value": 2,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Carbon emissions must peak by 2025 and be roughly halved by 2030 to set the world on track for a world that is 1.5 degrees Celsius warmer than pre-industrial levels.",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
            "value": 3,
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
